text: Terre-de-Bancalié is a commune. It is in Occitanie in the Tarn department in south France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Roumégoux (the seat), Ronel, Saint-Antonin-de-Lacalm, Saint-Lieux-Lafenasse, Terre-Clapier and Le Travet.Arrêté préfectoral 29 November 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Tarn
title: Terre-de-Bancalié
